# LOCAL FILES - DO NOT COMMIT TO GITHUB

This document explains which files should stay LOCAL ONLY and not be pushed to GitHub.

---

## Files to Keep LOCAL (Not in GitHub)

### 1. Skill Files
```
hiremitra-skill/
├── SKILL.md
└── README.md
```
**Why local?** - Internal reference only. Not needed in production.

### 2. Internal Guides
```
REBRANDING_GUIDE.md     ← Keep private
TESTING_GUIDE.md        ← Internal testing
UI_IMPROVEMENTS.md      ← Internal documentation
```

---

## .gitignore Configuration

✅ Both `backend/.gitignore` and `frontend/.gitignore` have been updated to EXCLUDE:

```gitignore
# Local Skills & Documentation (Keep Private)
hiremitra-skill/
REBRANDING_GUIDE.md
TESTING_GUIDE.md
UI_IMPROVEMENTS.md
```

---

## What WILL be in GitHub

The following directories/files WILL be committed:

✅ `backend/`
  - server.js
  - models/
  - controllers/
  - routes/
  - config/
  - package.json
  - .env (NO! Use .env.example)

✅ `frontend/`
  - app/
  - components/
  - lib/
  - hooks/
  - public/
  - package.json
  - .env.local (NO! Use .env.example)

---

## Using .env Files Safely

Instead of committing `.env`, create example templates:

### `backend/.env.example`
```
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/hiremitra-platform
PORT=5000
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_here
NODE_ENV=development
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

### `frontend/.env.local.example`
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

**Then in .gitignore:**
```gitignore
.env
.env.local
```

---

## Before Pushing to GitHub

Run this checklist:

```bash
# Check what will be committed
git status

# Verify these folders are NOT in the commit:
# ❌ hiremitra-skill/
# ❌ REBRANDING_GUIDE.md
# ❌ TESTING_GUIDE.md
# ❌ UI_IMPROVEMENTS.md

# Check .gitignore is working
git check-ignore hiremitra-skill/
# Should return: hiremitra-skill/
```

---

## Git Commands

### Check if file is ignored
```bash
git check-ignore -v hiremitra-skill/
```

### If accidentally added, remove from git:
```bash
git rm --cached hiremitra-skill/ -r
git rm --cached REBRANDING_GUIDE.md
git rm --cached TESTING_GUIDE.md
git rm --cached UI_IMPROVEMENTS.md

git commit -m "Remove local files from git tracking"
```

### Stage and commit only public files:
```bash
git add backend/ frontend/ README.md
git commit -m "Add HireMitra platform code"
git push origin main
```

