## Summary

✅ **DO push to GitHub:**
- All application code (backend, frontend)
- Configuration templates (.env.example)
- README and documentation
- git commits and history

❌ **DO NOT push to GitHub:**
- hiremitra-skill/ (internal reference)
- REBRANDING_GUIDE.md (internal)
- TESTING_GUIDE.md (internal)
- .env (actual secrets)
- .env.local (actual secrets)
- node_modules/

---

## Verification

Before your first GitHub push, verify:

```bash
cd hiremitra-platform

# List all files that will be pushed
git ls-files

# Should NOT contain:
# - hiremitra-skill/
# - REBRANDING_GUIDE.md
# - TESTING_GUIDE.md
# - UI_IMPROVEMENTS.md
```

If you see any of those files, they weren't properly ignored. Run `git check-ignore -v <filename>` to debug.

